    <keyword>snapshots directory</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Snapshot Operations</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Automatic snapshots</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Periodic <text styleclass="Code Example">auto_*.axpsnap</text> saves are on by default. Disable them for clean cold-boot / profiling runs:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">--autosnapshot off # or EMULATR_AUTOSNAP=off</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">On startup the newest snapshot is auto-loaded unless you force a cold boot:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">--no-autoload # or EMULATR_NO_AUTOLOAD=1</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Disabling autosnapshot on mint cold-boot runs avoids the per-save disk cost.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Creating snapshots</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Two capture mechanisms beyond the automatic saves:</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">- Console marker -- arm with EMULATR_CONSOLE_SNAPSHOT=1; when a console input line matches the marker (default &quot;set oem_string snapshot&quot;), a snapshots/predig_oemsnap_cyc&lt;N&gt;.axpsnap is written. Change the marker with EMULATR_SNAPSHOT_MARKER (leading / trailing whitespace trimmed; internal whitespace is NOT normalized).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> PC-triggered -- --snapshot-on-pc &lt;pc&gt;[,...], optionally named with --snapshot-name-tag &lt;s&gt;.</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Restoring snapshots</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">By default, startup restores the newest snapshot automatically (autoload-newest). To ignore snapshots and force a genuine cold boot, launch with <text styleclass="Code Example">--no-autoload</text> (<text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_NO_AUTOLOAD=1</text>). Snapshot files are resolved in the CWD-relative <text styleclass="Code Example">snapshots/</text> directory, so launch from the Emulatr root for the canonical set.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Pruning snapshots</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Pruning of old snapshots is off by default -- without the gate, <text styleclass="Code Example">pruneOldSnapshots</text> is a no-op and nothing is evicted. Enable it with:</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_SNAPSHOT_PRUNE=1</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
